We start from the Qwen3-1.7B, 4B, 8B, and 30B-A3B base models. To adapt these models for downstream tasks, we adopt a two-stage training strategy:
\begin{enumerate}
    \item \textbf{CPT:} We first continue pre-training each base model on a 50B-token subset randomly sampled from the 1T-token corpus described in Appendix~\ref{sec:appendix_study_i}, using a context length of 4096 with packed sequences.
    \item \textbf{SFT:} The models undergo SFT on the same 4B-token instruction-following dataset as Appendix~\ref{sec:appendix_study_i}.
\end{enumerate}
这里可能有一些语法错误。包括说那个sft 4B dataset和 Appendix~\ref{sec:appendix_study_i} 是一样的。你看看应该怎么表述？

The authors observed that Autoregression is mathematically a special case of Masked Diffusion where the masking order is deterministic (left-to-right) rather than random.
他们给出了AR的一般训练目标：
\begin{equation}
\label{eq:ar_loss}
    \mathcal{L}_{AR}^{1:N}=-\sum_{n=1}^N(\mathbf{x}_0^n)^\top\log f_\theta(\mathbf{x}_0^{1:n-1})_{n-1}
\end{equation}
以及 MDLM 在 t 时刻的 loss:
\begin{equation}
\label{eq:diffullama_loss}
    \mathcal{L}_t^{1:N}=\frac{1}{t}\mathbb{E}_{q(\mathbf{x}_t|\mathbf{x}_0)}\left[-\sum_{n=1}^N\delta_{\mathbf{x}_t^n,\boldsymbol{m}}(\mathbf{x}_0^n)^\top\log f_\theta(\mathbf{x}_t^{1:N})_n\right]
\end{equation}
他们发现 Eq.~\ref{eq:diffullama_loss} 本质上是 Eq.~\ref{eq:ar_loss} 的 reweight cross entropy loss 形式，加上了 indicator function, 这使得他们具有了motivation: 从一个 pretrained AR 直接转成 MDLM.

这个是我大概想的一段文字，你看看应该怎么表述成学术语言？

\section{Conclusion}
The era of diffusion for language has arrived. The trajectory from the theoretical foundations of MDLM, through the massive scaling of diffusion, to the efficient hybrid systems of Block Diffusion, demonstrates a rapid maturation of the technology.
While AR models likely remain the default for simple, streaming chat applications due to their established infrastructure, Diffusion Language Models are poised to take over in domains requiring:
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Complex Reasoning:} Where ``thinking before speaking" (global planning) is essential.
    \item \textbf{High-Throughput Serving:} Where parallel generation offers massive cost savings.
    \item \textbf{Controllable Generation:} Where infilling and specific lexical constraints are required.
\end{itemize}
这一段话不太好，不太符合学术论文的规范，分点太散。一般结论似乎不太用itemize，请你把相关内容扩充一下，然后变成自然流畅的，不分点的语言。

\section{Conclusion}
Diffusion language models have rapidly progressed from early theoretical formulations (e.g., MDLM) to large-scale training and, more recently, to system-oriented hybrid designs such as blockwise diffusion. This trajectory suggests that diffusion-based generation is becoming an increasingly practical alternative to token-level autoregression, especially when one cares about efficiency and controllability at inference time.

That said, autoregressive models will likely remain a strong default in settings that prioritize simplicity and strictly streaming generation, benefiting from mature training objectives and deeply optimized deployment stacks. In contrast, diffusion-style generation is particularly attractive in regimes where global constraints and holistic planning matter, where higher throughput can be obtained via parallel updates, or where controllability is central (e.g., infilling and enforcing lexical or structural constraints). We hope this work helps bridge the gap between the modeling advantages of diffusion and the practicality of modern AR backbones, and encourages further research on scalable, deployable diffusion paradigms for language.
